Sicilian Chicken
Chicken is the simplest ingredient to work with because it can be used in a
thousand different ways. This Sicilian chicken is juicy and tender and will
brighten any mealtime effortlessly. It’s healthy and flavorsome and hits the
right notes beautifully.
Serving Size: 4
Cooking Time: 50 Minutes
Ingredients:
4 boneless chicken breast fillets
14 oz. of quartered marinated artichoke hearts, jarred
1 sliced red onion
2 oz. of chopped capers
18 oz. of new baby potatoes, halved
8 oz. of chopped tomatoes
1 thinly sliced squash
1 thinly sliced zucchini
½ cup of pitted and sliced olives
½ cup of white wine
½ cup of chicken broth
2 tablespoons of olive oil
4 teaspoons of ground cumin
3 tablespoons of finely chopped basil
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit and fill a large
mixing bowl ¾ of the way with hot water. Add the baby
potatoes to the bowl and cover them with saran wrap, then put
them in the microwave for 3 minutes.
2. Add oil to a deep pan and gently heat it at a medium
temperature for 60 seconds.
3. Remove the potatoes from the microwave and put them into
the pan with the tomatoes, olives, artichokes, onion, capers,
zucchini, and squash. Season them generously with salt and
pepper and cook for 5 minutes, but stir them often so they
cook evenly.
4. Sprinkle salt, pepper, and cumin on both sides of the chicken
then place it on top of the vegetables. Pour the broth and wine
into the pan and cook for a good 35-40 minutes or until the
chicken is cooked through.
5. Finish with a sprinkle of basil on top.
