Beefsteak (Bistecca alla Fiorentina)
Fiorentina steak is delightful and a true Italian classic. T-bone steaks are
often the number one choice for this dish but porterhouse steaks work just
as well. While typically served rare, you could choose medium-rare or welldone, just remember to alter your cooking times slightly. Throw in a small
salad and you’ve got a great meal for any busy or slow evening.
This is sure to be a crowd-pleaser.
Serving Size: 2
Cooking Time: 15 Minutes
Ingredients:
35 oz. of T-bone steak (1-inch thick)
½ cup of olive oil
2 slices of white bread, cubed and with the crusts removed
24 oz. of chopped romaine lettuce
1 cubed bell pepper
½ cup of grated parmesan cheese
½ cup of pitted and halved black olives
1 chopped red onion
8 oz. of sliced fresh tomatoes
1 teaspoon of sugar
1 teaspoon of crushed chili flakes
½ teaspoon of garlic powder
3 tablespoons of red wine vinegar
2 ½ tablespoons of finely chopped basil
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit for 7-10
minutes, then coat the bread with 1 tablespoon of olive oil.
Scatter the bread on a baking sheet and bake it in the oven for
8-12 minutes to make croutons. Remove and set them aside to
cool once ready.
2. Heat a griddle pan at a medium-to-high temperature for 2-3
minutes, then season the steak with salt and pepper. Rub 1
tablespoon of oil on top then add to the grill and sear for 3
minutes. Flip the steak over and cook for a further 3 minutes.
Cooking times, however, depend on the size and thickness of
the steak. You can cook a few minutes longer on each side if
you prefer a medium-rare steak.
3. Remove the steak from the griddle pan and let it rest for 10
minutes.
4. Add the remaining oil to a measuring jug and combine it with
red wine vinegar, sugar, garlic powder, 5 teaspoons of
parmesan, chili flakes, 1 teaspoon of basil, and a pinch of salt
and pepper. Whisk well until a thin dressing forms.
5. Add the lettuce, bell pepper, onion, tomatoes, olives,
croutons, and the remaining parmesan to a large serving bowl.
Use salad tongs to toss to combine then drizzle the dressing
on top to create the ultimate Italian salad.
6. Slice the steak and serve alongside the salad. Finish with a
sprinkle of basil on top.
