Mozzarella, Red Onion, and Bacon Calzone
Calzones are fun, filling, and super tasty. It’s different but one you will love
to have time and again. Use different fillings to keep them appealing or
stick to your favorite fillings and you’re guaranteed to enjoy every time.
You can enjoy them any night of the week, regardless of how busy you
might be.
Serving Size: 2
Cooking Time: 20-25 Minutes
Ingredients:
6 oz. of thinly sliced mozzarella cheese
12 oz. of passata
2 ½ tablespoons of sunflower oil
2 chopped tomatoes
4 chopped bacon rashers
3 beaten eggs
2 ½ teaspoons of baking powder
10 oz. of plain flour
10 oz. of sliced pepperoni
2 oz. of finely grated cheddar cheese
2 finely diced jalapeno peppers
1 sliced red onion
2 teaspoons of Italian seasoning
2 tablespoons of water
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Heat a skillet at a medium temperature for 1 minute then add
the bacon and gently fry it for 5 minutes. Remove it from the
skillet and set it on paper towels to drain any excess grease or
fat from the bacon.
2. Add the beaten eggs to a large mixing bowl then combine it
with oil, baking powder, a pinch of salt and pepper, and all but
2 tablespoons of flour until a dough begins to form. This
might take 2-3 minutes, depending on how quickly the dough
comes together. You might need to add a tablespoon or two of
water to thin the dough out as well.
3. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit and place a large
baking sheet in the oven to heat through for 10 minutes.
4. Use 2 tablespoons of flour to dust a clean surface then split
the dough into two equal-sized pieces. Roll each piece of
dough into 10-inch semi-thick consistencies.
5. Spread the passata on each dough piece then sprinkle 1
teaspoon of Italian seasoning on top of the sauce. Spread the
mozzarella, bacon, onion, pepperoni, tomatoes, cheddar
cheese, jalapeno, and a pinch of salt and pepper on each
calzone then carefully fold the dough over and seal the edges
with a fork.
6. Remove the baking sheet from the oven and place it on a
cooling rack for a moment while you carefully place each
calzone onto it. Place the calzones in the oven to bake for a
good 20 minutes.
7. Remove and serve immediately to enjoy the full flavor of the
calzone.
