Fish Puttanesca (Pesce alla Puttanesca)
One of the most delicate Italian meals to serve has to be Pesce alla
Puttanesca. The tilapia brings beautiful flavors and never disappoints. It’s a
rustic dish but one that will leave you wanting more. For those who want to
make mealtimes a little more interesting, this is the dish for you. It’s
gorgeous and easy to prepare.
Serving Size: 4
Cooking Time: 35 Minutes
Ingredients:
18 oz. of tilapia fillets, halved
1 white diced onion
3 oz. of chopped anchovies
32 oz. of crushed tomatoes, canned
8 minced garlic cloves
3 tablespoons of olive oil
10 slices of thick-cut rustic bread
10 teaspoons of garlic butter
½ cup of dry white wine
1 tablespoon of rinsed and drained capers
1 cup of pitted and halved olives
5 tablespoons of finely chopped parsley
1 teaspoon of ground oregano
¼ teaspoon of cinnamon
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Pour the oil into a large pan or soup pot and gently heat it at a
medium temperature for 1 minute. When the oil is hot, add the
onions and cook them for 6 minutes, then add the garlic and
cook for a further 1 minute.
2. Add the anchovies to the pan and cook them for 3 minutes
and stir every minute to prevent anything from burning.
3. Pour the wine into the pan and cook for 2-3 minutes (as this
will burn off the alcohol element), then mix in the cinnamon,
oregano, and tomatoes. Let the mixture simmer for a good 10
minutes and stir every few minutes.
4. Add the capers and olives and cook them for 2 minutes.
Season the mixture with salt and pepper then mix in half of
the parsley and cook for 1 minute more.
5. Rub salt and pepper on the tilapia fillets then add them to the
pan. Spoon the sauce over the fish and cover and cook for 8
minutes or until the tilapia is cooked through.
6. Spread the garlic butter on the bread then remove the
puttanesca from the heat and divide onto plates. Top with the
remaining parsley and serve the bread on the side to finish.
