Mascarpone and Tomato Crispy Cod Bake
A fish bake might not sound overly exciting but this beautiful Italianinspired one will make mealtime fun. While this mascarpone and tomato
crispy cod bake is simple it combines beautiful flavors to create a standout
dish.
Cod can also be substituted for any white fish if you so wish.
Serving Size: 4
Cooking Time: 20 Minutes
Ingredients:
4 cod fillets
32 oz. of chopped tomatoes, canned
2 oz. of breadcrumbs
10 oz. of mascarpone cheese
3 minced garlic cloves
2 tablespoons of olive oil
8 slices of thick-cut rustic bread
3 tablespoons of finely chopped basil
2 tablespoons of roughly chopped parsley
8, 1-inch-thick slices of mozzarella cheese
2 oz. of parmigiano Reggiano cheese
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. To create the mascarpone and tomato sauce, add oil to a
saucepan and gently heat it for 30 seconds. Add the garlic and
fry it for 2 minutes to help release the aromas better.
2. Put the tomatoes into the saucepan and bring them to a boil at
a medium heat, then let them simmer and cook for 6-7
minutes. Stir the mascarpone and basil into the pan and mix
well until a creamy sauce-like texture forms. This might take
2 or 3 minutes to achieve.
3. Season the cod with salt and pepper then add it to the pan and
bring it to a boil. Mix in the parsley and let it simmer for a
good 10 minutes.
4. Preheat your grill to a medium temperature for 5 minutes,
then combine the breadcrumbs and Parmigiano Reggiano
cheese to create a topping for the fish.
5. Remove the cod from the heat and layer the mozzarella on top
of the cod. Sprinkle the breadcrumb mixture on top and put
under the grill for 5 minutes to finish cooking.
6. Divide the puttanesca onto plates and serve with a few slices
of thick-cut bread.
