Roman Pasta (Cacio E Pepe)
Cozy with the traditional flavors of Italy, this cheese and pepper pasta is a
dish that’ll make mealtimes a lot more appealing. It’s a simple but quality
dish to enjoy today.
Serving Size: 4-6
Cooking Time: 10 Minutes
Ingredients:
3 cups of finely grated pecorino cheese
16 oz. of spaghetti pasta
4 tablespoons of crushed black peppercorns
Salt for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Put the crushed peppercorns into a skillet and toast them at a
medium temperature for 3 minutes. You want to move the
peppercorns every few minutes with a wooden spoon so they
don’t burn.
2. Remove the peppercorns from the heat and set them aside on
a plate for a few moments.
3. Pour cold water into a large pot, filling it to 75% capacity, and
season with a pinch of salt. Heat the water over medium-high
heat until it reaches a rolling boil. Subsequently, stir in the
spaghetti and allow it to cook for 7 minutes.
4. Drain the pasta once it’s ready but retain at least 2 or 3 cups of
cooking liquid.
5. Add 1 cup of cooking liquid to a second saucepan and heat it
at a medium temperature for 1 minute then add the pecorino
cheese and melt. Stir the cheese as it melts until it creates a
creamy ricotta-like consistency. Season with a pinch of salt,
then add ¼ cup of water if the sauce is too thick.
6. Put the peppercorns into the pan and heat them through with
the sauce for 2 minutes. Add 4 tablespoons of water then put
the spaghetti into the sauce. Heat it through for a minute then
remove and serve immediately.
