Stuffed Manicotti
Manicotti is great for vegetarians and meat eaters alike. It’s comforting but
delicious and will be a great dish for everyone to enjoy. Plus, there are lots
of different flavor combinations to try that will liven up any dinner table.
Serving Size: 4
Cooking Time: 1 Hour 40 Minutes
Ingredients:
10 manicotti pasta tubes
10 oz. of washed and torn spinach leaves
1 ½ cups of ricotta cheese
2 cups of shredded parmesan cheese
32 oz. of chopped tomatoes, canned
1 finely diced red onion
7 minced garlic cloves
¾ cup of red wine
2 tablespoons of finely chopped basil
4 tablespoons of olive oil
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Add 3 tablespoons of oil to a large pan and heat at a medium
temperature for 60 seconds, then add the diced onions and
garlic and cook them for a good 7 minutes. Stir often so they
don’t burn, then add the basil, tomatoes, and wine. Cover and
cook for 40 minutes to create a thin sauce.
2. Fill a large pan with water and a pinch of salt, then bring it to
a boil at a medium-to-high temperature. Add the manicotti
pasta to the pan and cook for 10 minutes as the water
continues to boil.
3. Add 1 tablespoon of oil to a saucepan and gently heat it at a
medium temperature for 60 seconds. Put the spinach into the
pan and cook it for 3 minutes or until it begins to wilt.
4. Remove the spinach from the heat and drain the excess oil.
Add the ricotta to the pan and season with a pinch of salt and
pepper then combine with the spinach to create the manicotti
filling.
5. Preheat your oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit then remove the
manicotti sauce from the heat and use an immersion blender
to thin the sauce out (if necessary). You may not have to do
this, depending on the consistency of the sauce. Add a pinch
of salt and pepper and give the mixture one final stir.
6. Drain the manicotti pasta thoroughly then carefully fill each
with the spinach and ricotta cheese mixture.
7. Pour ¾ of the manicotti sauce onto a baking dish then add the
manicotti-filled pasta and pour the remaining sauce on top.
Sprinkle the parmesan over the pasta then cover with
aluminum foil and bake in the oven for 35-40 minutes.
