Eggplant Parmesan
For those who want a comfort dish, eggplant parmesan has to be it. It’s
incredible and really makes mealtimes enjoyable. It’s simple to make but
tastes fantastic and will be a beloved dinner by all.
Serving Size: 4-6
Cooking Time: 50 Minutes
Ingredients:
1 thinly sliced eggplant
8 cups of tomato and basil pasta sauce
2 beaten eggs
1 cup of finely grated parmesan cheese
½ cup of breadcrumbs
1 ¼ cup of flour
Cooking spray
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit then grease 2
ovenproof dishes with cooking spray.
2. Crack and beat the eggs in one bowl, then add flour to a
second bowl and combine it with a pinch of salt and pepper.
3. Coat each slice of eggplant in the flour mixture then dip it in
the egg and place it into one of the greased dishes. Put the
eggplant in the oven for 10-12 minutes but put the second
dish in the oven as well so that it can heat through.
4. Remove the eggplant from the oven and reduce your oven to
350 degrees Fahrenheit.
5. Remove the dish from the oven and place it on a cooling rack
for a moment. Pour half of the pasta sauce into the bottom of
the dish, then add a layer of eggplant followed by the
remaining sauce.
6. Sprinkle half of the parmesan on top and cover with
aluminum foil. Bake the eggplant parmesan in the oven for 15
minutes.
7. Combine the remaining parmesan with breadcrumbs, then
remove the dish from the oven. Discard the foil and sprinkle
the parmesan and breadcrumb mixture on top.
8. Bake uncovered for a further 10 minutes.
9. Once cooked, remove from the oven and let it rest for 7-10
minutes before serving.
