Tuna, Capers, and Chili Linguine
Linguine is a staple of Italian cuisine but it is also one of the more adaptable
ingredients to work with too. This tuna, capers, and chili linguine is fun,
healthy, and delicious. It’s one dish you’ll love to make for all the family.
Serving Size: 2
Cooking Time: 15 Minutes
Ingredients:
8 oz. of linguine pasta
1 freshly diced tomato
8 oz. of drained tuna, canned
2 teaspoons of drained and chopped capers
1 diced red chili pepper
1 minced garlic clove
The zest of 1 lemon
4 oz. of washed rocket leaves
3 tablespoons of finely chopped parsley
1 tablespoon of olive oil
The juice of 1 lemon
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Fill a pan with water and a pinch of salt then bring it to a boil
at a medium-to-high heat. Once the water boils, add the
linguine and cook it for a good 6-7 minutes at a medium heat.
2. Once ready, remove the linguine from the heat and drain it but
retain at least 1 cup of cooking liquid.
3. Add oil to a pan and gently heat it at a low temperature for 1
minute. Add the chili pepper and garlic and cook them for 2
minutes but stir them often to prevent them from burning.
4. Add the linguine and ½ cup of cooking liquid to the pan and
toss to mix with the chili and garlic. Put the tuna, capers, and
lemon zest into the pan and season with a pinch of salt and
pepper then cook for 2 minutes.
5. Mix in the lemon juice, rocket, and tomatoes and cook for 1
minute more. Then remove and top with parsley to finish.
