Lasagna Soup
Lasagna lovers will adore this soup. It’s hearty and comforting and comes
with everything you’d want in a lasagna soup. While it does sound strange,
this soup is a wonderful dish that’ll make mealtimes a lot more interesting.
Serving Size: 6-8
Cooking Time: 40 Minutes
Ingredients:
24 oz. of ground beef
10 oz. of lasagna noodles, broken into small squares
7 minced garlic cloves
3 diced shallots
18 oz. of crushed tomatoes, canned
18 oz. of diced Roma tomatoes
4 tablespoons of tomato puree
10 oz. of ricotta cheese
8 oz. of finely shredded mozzarella cheese
4 oz. of finely grated parmesan cheese
6 cups of chicken stock
2 tablespoons of olive oil
1 teaspoon of ground thyme
1 teaspoon of ground oregano
1 teaspoon of crushed red chili pepper flakes
4 oz. of chopped basil
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Pour 1 tablespoon of oil into a skillet and heat it at a mediumto-high temperature for 30 seconds. Add the ground beef and
brown it for a good 7 minutes. Season the beef well with salt
and pepper and use a wooden spoon or spatula to break the
meat up as it cooks so that it browns evenly.
2. Once the beef is browned fully, remove it from the heat and
carefully drain any fat from the skillet. Set the beef to one
side for a few moments.
3. Add the remaining oil to a large soup pot and heat it at a
medium temperature for 1 minute. Put the shallots into the pot
and cook them for 3-4 minutes or until they’ve softened, then
add the garlic and cook for 2 minutes.
4. Pour the stock into the pot and stir well, then mix in the diced
tomatoes, tomato puree, crushed tomatoes, thyme, oregano,
chili flakes, and ¾ of the basil. Add the beef to the pot and
mix well to combine.
5. Bring the soup to a boil then reduce to a low-to-medium heat.
Cover and let the soup simmer gently for 20 minutes.
6. Pour water into a pan and bring to boil at a medium-to-high
heat, then add the egg noodles and cook them for 7 minutes.
7. In a bowl, combine the mozzarella, ricotta, and parmesan
cheese.
8. Drain the pasta and mix it into the soup with the remaining
basil, then divide it into bowls and top it off with the cheese
mixture to finish.
