Onion, Sausage, Potato, and Pepper Bake
Comforting, with lots of interesting flavors vying for your attention, this
onion, sausage, potato, and pepper bake will brighten up mealtimes. It’s a
dish that everyone will enjoy and can be adapted to suit whatever you have
available at home. Plus, this bake is super easy to make even on a busy
weeknight.
Serving Size: 10
Cooking Time: 45 Minutes
Ingredients:
32 oz. of Italian or Kielbasa sausages, sliced thickly (around
2-inches)
6 peeled and sliced potatoes
5 thinly sliced bell peppers
4 white onions sliced into thin wedges
4 peeled and diced carrots
2 sprigs of thyme
2 teaspoons of ground rosemary
2 teaspoons of oregano
1 teaspoon of ground basil
¾ cup of vegetable stock
½ cup of olive oil
¾ cup of dry white wine
Cooking spray
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit then grease an
ovenproof casserole dish with cooking spray.
2. Pour 1 tablespoon of oil into a skillet and heat it at a medium
temperature for 30 seconds, then add the sausages and brown
them for 7-8 minutes. Flip the sausages over every 2 minutes
so that both sides cook evenly.
3. Once the sausages are browned, remove them from the heat
and drain any excess fat from them. Then put the sausages
into the greased casserole dish.
4. Pour the remaining oil into the skillet and heat for 30 seconds
before adding the potatoes. Cook them for a good 5 minutes
but stir them often, then add the bell peppers, onions, and
carrots, and continue to cook for 5-6 minutes.
5. Remove the potatoes, onions, carrots, and bell peppers from
the heat and pour them into the casserole dish.
6. Pour the stock and wine into the casserole dish, then mix in
the oregano, basil, rosemary, and a pinch of salt and pepper.
Add the sprigs of thyme then place in the oven for 25
minutes.
7. Once cooked, remove the bake from the oven and lightly
season, if necessary, to finish.
