Pan Seared Steaks with Onions, Radishes, and
Tomatoes
With Italian influences, these steaks with onions, radishes, and tomatoes are
just gorgeous. It’s a dish that’ll liven up any dinner table and leave you
wanting more.
Serving Size: 2
Cooking Time: 15 Minutes
Ingredients:
2, 8 oz. steaks
1 sliced white onion
2 thinly sliced radishes
14 oz. of fresh quartered tomatoes
¾ cup of red wine
4 oz. of butter
1 tablespoon of olive oil
1 diced red chili pepper
3 tablespoons of finely chopped basil
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Heat a skillet at a medium-to-high temperature for 2 minutes,
then add half of the butter and let it melt for a few seconds.
2. Season the steaks generously with salt and pepper then add
them to the hot skillet. Cook the steaks for a good 4 minutes
then flip them over and cook for a further 4 minutes. Spoon
the butter over the steaks as they cook as this helps make
them juicer. Cooking times for the steaks, however, will
depend on your preferences.
3. Remove the steaks from the pan and set them on a chopping
board to rest for 8-10 minutes.
4. Add oil to the skillet (that you cooked the steaks in) and heat
it at a low-to-medium temperature for 1 minute then add the
sliced onions and cook them for 10-12 minutes.
5. Put the remaining butter into a saucepan and melt it at a
medium heat for 1 minute. Add the radishes and season them
with a pinch of salt and pepper, then cook them for 10
minutes but flip halfway through.
6. Add the wine to the pan and gently bring it to the boil. Let the
pan simmer for 3 minutes to burn the alcohol from the wine,
then add the tomatoes and diced chili pepper and cook for a
further 3-5 minutes.
7. Slice the steaks then add them and the onions to the pan with
the radishes. Mix well then let the steaks briefly heat through
for 30-60 seconds.
8. Remove and top with basil to finish.
