Sauteed Mushrooms, Onions, and Peppers
While this would be typically a side dish in Italy, it works perfectly as a
main meal too. It’s hearty, filling, and bursting with Mediterranean flavors.
This is a dish that’s perfect for any night of the week and can be pretty
versatile too.
Serving Size: 2
Cooking Time: 10 Minutes
Ingredients:
32 oz. of sliced button mushrooms
1 diced red onion
1 finely sliced bell pepper
12 oz. of spinach leaves
2 cups of Italian dressing
2 teaspoons of oregano
1 diced chili pepper
4 oz. of chopped parsley
2 tablespoons of soft butter
4 tablespoons of water
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. Heat a large skillet at a medium-to-high temperature for 1
minute, then add the butter and mushrooms. Season them with
a pinch of salt and pepper then cook for 7 minutes. Coat the
mushrooms in the butter then add the bell pepper, chili
pepper, and diced onions to the skillet, then cook them for 3
minutes.
2. Mix the Italian dressing and oregano into the skillet and cook
for a further 4-5 minutes, then add the water and spinach and
cook it for around 3-4 minutes or until it begins to wilt.
3. Remove the skillet from the heat and finish with a sprinkle of
parsley on top.
