Homemade Diavolo Pizza
Homemade pizzas are fun, simple, and so easy to make. You can get
everyone involved in making it and it’s just a great option for dinner. The
Diavolo – devil’s pizza – is gorgeous. It has the right amount of heat and
spiciness to it and you can easily switch around toppings if you want to.
Serving Size: 1-2
Cooking Time: 15 Minutes
Ingredients:
2 ¾ cups of flour
¾ cup of water
½ teaspoon of rapid-rise or instant yeast
3 tablespoons of olive oil
½ teaspoon of salt
½ cup of spicy pizza sauce
4 oz. of shredded mozzarella cheese
¼ cup of pitted and chopped olives
2 sliced hot chili peppers
12 slices of spicy salami
½ teaspoon of crushed black pepper (optional)
Instructions:
1. To a stand mixer, add 2 ½ cups of flour, salt, and yeast. Use a
dough hook to gently mix the flour, then slowly add the water
and 2 tablespoons of oil. Knead until a dough forms (around
5-6 minutes on a low speed).
2. Grease a bowl with the remaining tablespoon of oil then
remove the dough from the mixer and place it in the bowl.
Cover the bowl with saran wrap and let it rise for 2 ½ hours.
3. Remove the dough from the bowl then sprinkle the remaining
flour on a clean surface and gently roll the dough into a ball
shape. Cover the dough with saran wrap and let it rest for 30
minutes more.
4. Preheat your oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit then roll the
dough out into a 12-inch medium-thick base. Put the base on a
large baking sheet then place it in the oven for 5 minutes to
crisp up.
5. Remove the pizza from the oven then place it on a cooling
rack for a moment. Pour the sauce on the base but stop around
an inch from the edge. You might not need all of the sauce; it
depends on how much you prefer to use.
6. Sprinkle the mozzarella cheese on the pizza, then add the
salami, hot chili peppers, and olives. If you want to add a little
more heat, sprinkle a pinch of pepper on top too. Place the
pizza in the oven for 8-12 minutes or until cooked to your
liking.
