Chicken Parmesan
Want a meat version of the eggplant parmesan? This chicken parmesan is
exceptional. Mozzarella, marinara sauce, and chicken, there is really no
better combo. It’s tender and will liven up your mealtimes. While you can
opt for pre-made marinara sauce, making one from scratch is fun and easier
than it sounds.
Serving Size: 4-6
Cooking Time: 50 Minutes
Ingredients:
4 boneless chicken breast fillets, halved
32 oz. of crushed tomatoes, canned
¾ teaspoon of dried oregano
7 tablespoons of olive oil
2 ½ cups of grated mozzarella cheese
1 ½ tablespoons of finely minced basil
1 small diced white onion
5 minced garlic cloves
¾ cup of breadcrumbs
¾ cup of all-purpose flour
¾ cup of finely grated parmesan cheese
1 teaspoon of ground cumin
¾ teaspoon of red chili powder
16 oz. of spaghetti
3 eggs
2 tablespoons of finely chopped parsley
Cooking spray
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
1. To create a marinara sauce, add diced onions and 3
tablespoons of olive oil to a saucepan and fry them for 6
minutes. Mix the garlic into the pan and cook for a further 2
minutes.
2. Add the tomatoes to the pan, then mix in the chili powder,
oregano, basil, cumin, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir well
to combine then bring the mixture to a gentle boil. Cover with
the lid and simmer gently on a low heat for 15-20 minutes or
until a marinara-like texture is formed. Remove the sauce
from the heat and set aside for a moment.
3. Add flour to a bowl and season it with a pinch of salt and
pepper. In a second bowl, break and whisk the eggs for 15-20
seconds. In a third bowl, add the breadcrumbs and combine
them with parmesan.
4. Preheat your oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit then grease a
baking dish with cooking spray and place it in the oven for 10
minutes.
5. Pour the remaining oil into a large pan and gently heat it at a
medium temperature for 2-3 minutes.
6. Wrap the chicken in saran wrap and gently pound it for 30
seconds with a cooking mallet to tenderize the meat so they
have the same thickness. Unwrap the chicken then dip each
piece into the flour, followed by the eggs, and finally the
breadcrumb mixture.
7. Add the coated chicken to the pan and cook it for 3 minutes.
