well for 1 minute. Pour the wine into the skillet and cook for
5-7 minutes, then mix in the anchovies, tomatoes, bell
peppers, mushrooms, jalapenos, basil, sugar, and a pinch of
pepper.
3. Bring the beef Bolognese to a boil then reduce to a low heat
and simmer gently for a good 20-22 minutes.
4. Put the spaghetti into a pan filled with water and bring it to a
boil. Once boiled, let the spaghetti cook for around 6-7
minutes. Once cooked, drain the pasta in a colander and set it
aside for a moment.
5. Pour the heavy cream and half of the parmesan into the
Bolognese and mix well to create a creamy sauce. Let the
sauce heat through for 1-2 minutes then add the spaghetti and
toss to mix through the sauce and Bolognese.
6. Remove the spaghetti Bolognese from the heat and divide it
into plates. Finish by sprinkling the remaining parmesan on
top.
