Italian Sausage Casserole
Want a family dinner that’s easy to make but has great Italian flavors? Well,
this Italian sausage casserole is perfect. It combines beautiful flavors and is
incredibly easy to make too. You will love this casserole and it’ll make
dinnertime fun.
Serving Size: 6-8
Cooking Time: 40 Minutes
Ingredients:
2 peeled and diced carrots
8 oz. of chopped button mushrooms
2 diced bell peppers
1 diced chili pepper
¼ cup of beef stock
24 oz. of sliced Italian sausages
18 oz. of chopped cauliflower
12 oz. of chopped broccoli florets
½ cup of finely chopped parsley
10 oz. of shredded mature cheddar cheese
8 oz. of soft cream cheese
1 tablespoon of olive oil
Salt and pepper for seasoning
Instructions:
Preheat your oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit then pour oil into a large
skillet. Heat the oil at a medium-to-high temperature for 1 minute then add
the carrots, mushrooms, bell peppers, chili pepper, broccoli, and stock, and
cook for 7 minutes.
Add the sausages to the skillet, season them with salt and pepper and cook
them for 10 minutes. It’s important you move and flip the sausages every
few minutes so that they brown evenly. Then mix the cream cheese into the
skillet and let it melt for 1-2 minutes.
Put the cauliflower into a blender and blitz it for 30-40 seconds or until fine
rice-like grains form.
Remove the sausages and vegetables from the heat then pour them into a
baking dish. Sprinkle half of the cheddar cheese into the dish and mix
around with the sausages and vegetables. Add the cauliflower rice and
remaining cheese then cover and bake for 25 minutes.
Remove the bake from the oven and cook uncovered for a further 10-15
minutes. Finish with a sprinkle of parsley on top.
