Chocolate Pudding (Budino al Cioccolato)
Indulgent, rich, and ever so tasty, this Italian pudding is one you don’t want
to miss out on. Budino al cioccolato is a perfect dessert for chocolate lovers
everywhere and you’ll love the silky-smooth texture of the pudding.
Serving Size: 4
Cooking Time: 10 Minutes
Ingredients:
5 oz. of chopped dark chocolate
7 tablespoons of butter
½ cup of caster sugar
1 ¾ cups of milk
3 tablespoons of cornstarch
4 mint leaves
Instructions:
1. Add the butter to a saucepan and let it melt for 1-2 minutes at
a medium heat. Stir it every so often to speed up the melting
process and ensure the butter doesn’t burn.
2. Slowly pour and whisk the sugar into the melted butter for a
minute or until it begins to thicken. Reduce to a low heat then
add the chocolate and stir for a good 3-5 minutes until it fully
melts. You must stir constantly as the chocolate melts so that
it doesn’t burn.
3. Pour the milk into a second saucepan and gently bring it to the
boil at a medium heat. It may take around 2-3 minutes to do
so.
4. Once the chocolate has melted, sift in the cornstarch and stir
for a good minute to ensure no lumps remain.
5. Remove the milk from the heat and slowly (and carefully)
pour it into the chocolate mixture. It’s important to do this
slowly otherwise the mixture might curdle. Increase to a
medium heat and continue stirring for 4-5 minutes or until the
chocolate pudding begins to thicken up.
6. Remove the pudding from the heat and carefully spoon it into
dessert glasses then set it aside to chill for an hour at room
temperature. Then put the pudding into the refrigerator for a
further 3 hours to firm up fully.
7. Serve with a few mint leaves on top to finish.
