Lemon Olive Oil Cake
Never had an olive oil cake? Well, you’ve been missing out because it’s one
of the best desserts to make at home. It’s a traditional cake of Italy and it is
truly sublime. This lemon olive oil cake is moist and surprisingly light but
has just the right amount of sweetness to it.
Serving Size: 8-10
Cooking Time: 1 Hour 15 Minutes
Ingredients:
2 ¼ cups of flour
2 cups of granulated sugar
1 ½ cups of whole milk
1 ½ cups of virgin olive oil
3 eggs
½ teaspoon of baking soda
½ teaspoon of baking powder
½ cup of limoncello
The zest of 1 lemon
½ cup of lemon juice
¼ teaspoon of salt
¼ cup of confectioners’ sugar
Cooking spray
Instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 325 degrees Fahrenheit then line a
circular 9-inch springform pan with parchment paper. Grease
the paper with cooking spray and set the pan to one side for a
few moments.
2. Crack the eggs into a mixing bowl then add the oil and whisk
them for 30-40 seconds or until they have incorporated with
one another. Add the milk, lemon juice, lemon zest, and
limoncello to the bowl and whisk well for a further 30
seconds.
3. Slowly pour the granulated sugar into the mixture, along with
the flour, salt, baking powder, and baking soda, then whisk
well until a thin batter forms. This might take 2 or 3 minutes
to achieve.
4. Pour the batter into the springform pan and smooth it out with
a spoon or spatula. Gently bang the pan on your worktop so
that you can release air trapped in the batter.
5. Place the cake in the oven to bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
You should, however, check on the cake after 1 hour as it can
cook faster depending on your appliance. Use a toothpick to
check on the cake: a clean toothpick indicates it’s cooked
inside.
6. Once cooked, remove the cake from the oven and set it aside
to cool on a cooling rack for 50-60 minutes. Remove the cake
from the springform pan and dust it with confectioners’ sugar
to finish.
