Pignoli
Pignoli is a classic Italian dessert that will impress and spoil those around
your dinner table. These are soft and chewy with a beautiful crispy outer
layer. It’s one you’ll adore and are great for those with a sweet tooth.
Serving Size: 16
Cooking Time: 20-25 Minutes
Ingredients:
1 ¾ cups of granulated sugar
18 oz. of almond paste
8 oz. of pine nuts
4 egg whites
¼ teaspoon of salt
Instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit and line 2
baking sheets with parchment paper.
2. To a food processor, add the almond paste and pulse it for 10-
12 seconds. Pour the sugar and salt into the processor and
pulse for a further 45 seconds.
3. Add 2 egg whites to the processor then mix for a further 30
seconds. Pour the remaining egg whites into the processor and
mix for a further 30-60 seconds or until a dough-like texture
forms.
4. Remove the pignoli dough from the food process and split it
into small circles. Roll each pignoli circle into the pine nuts to
form the crispy outer coating. Place the pignoli onto the
baking sheets but space them apart as they can expand as they
cook.
5. Put the pignoli into the oven for 15 minutes, then remove
them and let them cool down for 30 minutes before serving
them.
