Zeppole
For those who want a dessert that is tasty and indulgent, but not too heavy,
then zeppole is perfect. Zeppole is a beautiful deep-fried dough ball that is
light and full of flavor. It’s incredibly tasty and these make a wonderful
after-dinner treat.
Serving Size: 8-10
Cooking Time: 20 Minutes
Ingredients:
½ cup of confectioners’ sugar
1 ½ cups of all-purpose flour
¾ cup of soft butter
5 eggs
1 ¼ cup of water
½ teaspoon of salt
1 cup of olive oil
5 tablespoons of sugar
Instructions:
1. Preheat your deep-fat fryer to 375 degrees Fahrenheit then
add water, butter, sugar, and salt to a saucepan. If you don’t
have a fryer, fill a pot with 1 or 2 cups of oil and heat it until
it reaches 375 degrees Fahrenheit. Please note that you will
need a cooking thermometer to check the temperature.
2. Heat the butter and water mixture at a medium temperature
for 2-3 minutes. Stir constantly so that the butter and sugar
incorporate fully with the water. Once combined, reduce to a
low heat and slowly stir the flour into the pan until a dough
forms.
3. Remove the dough from the heat and carefully put it into a
bowl. Set the dough aside for 5-7 minutes to cool down.
4. Once cooled, carefully crack and mix the eggs (one at a time)
into the dough. Use a wooden spoon to combine the eggs into
the dough and be thorough. You don’t, however, want to add
the eggs if the dough is still warm otherwise the eggs will
cook and curdle.
5. Scoop a tablespoon or two of batter and shape it into a donut
or ball. Continue to do this until you have used all of the
batter to create the zeppole. Place them on a plate and set up a
wire cooling rack.
6. Put 5 zeppole dough pieces into the fryer and cook them for 6
minutes. Turn the zeppole over every 1-2 minutes until both
sides are golden brown. Once cooked, remove the zeppole
with a slotted spoon and place them on the wire rack to drain
excess oil from them.
7. Repeat the process until you have used up all of the zeppole
batter. Dust the zeppole with confectioners’ sugar to finish.
